The paper deals with the computation of group invariants, which is a topic in computational algebraic geometry and symbolic computation. The focus is on symplectic invariants, which are related to symplectic geometry and have applications in physics. Therefore, cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) and cs.SY (Symplectic Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the cost of computation and the need for on-the-fly optimization, which suggests that it may be relevant to cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
